{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "BlossomWire",
  "description": "Scene 3 probe - the scanned apricot blossom cluster as a true line wireframe, via the Wireframe-preset pipeline with meshes instead of polytopes: gltf_mesh_source -> rotate_3d (slow time spin) -> flatten_3d perspective -> draw_lines points, while node.mesh_edges (NEW atom, this branch: per-triangle edge topology from the flat triangle list, index arithmetic only) supplies draw_lines edges. TWO assets share the modelPath file-picker card, two distinct stage looks: blossom_wire_welded.glb (default; raw material-3 cluster welded at 1e-5 BEFORE decimation with UVs stripped pre-export - both required or the glTF exporter re-splits chart borders and quadric collapse floors at the ~13k island count, measured 2026-07-11 - then 321k->3126 tris, 9378 flat verts; reads as ONE connected polygonal net) and blossom_wire.glb (unwelded confetti cut, 3070 tris / 9210 flat verts; the scan's UV-chart islands drift apart under decimation into disconnected triangle sparkle - Peter's pick from the first render). gltf max_capacity is sized EXACTLY to the loaded asset (9378 covers both; the smaller asset under-fills the buffer and the zero tail draws dot edges at vertex 0 - swap max_capacity to 9210 if the confetti asset ever becomes the default; proper active-count plumbing is the tracked v1 limitation on node.mesh_edges).",
